⚙️ Algorithms
📌 Introduction

This section focuses on understanding and implementing fundamental algorithms used to solve computational problems efficiently. The goal is to develop strong problem-solving skills, improve logical thinking, and gain insights into optimizing solutions using different algorithmic approaches. It serves as a bridge between basic programming and advanced topics like data structures, competitive programming, and system design.

## Topics Covered

Recursion
Backtracking
Greedy Algorithms
Divide and Conquer
Searching Techniques
Sorting Techniques
Basic Optimization Strategies
Problem Decomposition

## Problem Statements

Find factorial of a number using recursion
Generate Fibonacci sequence using recursion
Solve Tower of Hanoi problem
Solve N-Queens problem (basic implementation)
Generate all subsets of a given set
Solve a simple maze (rat in a maze problem)
Activity Selection Problem
Minimum number of coins (coin change – greedy approach)
Implement Merge Sort
Implement Quick Sort
Find power of a number using fast exponentiation

## Note

This section is intended to build a deeper understanding of algorithmic thinking and efficient problem-solving techniques. Problems will be expanded to include more complex and optimized approaches over time.
